Master's Thesis is student's written work based on experimental and theoretical scientific research. Master's Thesis must be defended by the student  during his/her oral presentation to defence committee.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The goal of Master's Thesis is providing student with experience of research work, starting from planning of the activities until presentation of the results.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A person who has defended his/her Master's Thesis in Materials Science and Engineering has deep knowledge in some area of materials science, and has performed his/her independent research work in  this area. He/she can argue about his/her conclusions, and analyze professional opinions, consequences and generalizations published in press or media. He/she can make a public presentation and participate in discussions. He/she is acquainted with science ethics.
